==Ancient Greek==
===Etymology===
From ancient Greek '''Μακεδονία''' (''Makedonia'') "highland", from ancient Greek [[μακεδνός]] (''makednos'')  "high, tall", from Doric Greek [[μάκος]] (''makos'') "height, length" . In Ionian Greek: [[μήκος]] (''mekos'').

